## What was built: `@prisma/client-generator-rest-api`

### Package location
`packages/client-generator-rest-api/`

### Files created

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `package.json` | Package manifest with `workspace:*` deps on `@prisma/dmmf`, `@prisma/generator`, `@prisma/internals`, `@prisma/debug`; dual CJS/ESM exports |
| `tsconfig.json` / `tsconfig.build.json` | Mirror the pattern from `client-generator-js` |
| `helpers/build.ts` | One-liner that delegates to the shared `adapterConfig` build pipeline |
| `src/scalar-to-ts.ts` | Maps every Prisma scalar type (`Int`, `String`, `DateTime`, `Decimal`, …) to its TypeScript equivalent |
| `src/render-enums.ts` | Renders each Prisma enum as a TypeScript string union type (`export type Role = 'USER' \| 'ADMIN'`) |
| `src/render-model-interface.ts` | Produces four declarations per model: the flat **interface**, **CreateInput** (excludes auto-generated ids and `@updatedAt`), **UpdateInput** (all mutable fields optional), and **WhereUniqueInput** (union of all `@id`/`@unique` field selectors) |
| `src/render-model-client.ts` | Emits a typed `${Model}Client` class extending `BaseRestClient` with `findMany`, `findUnique`, `create`, `update`, `delete` methods wired to conventional REST endpoints |
| `src/render-base-infra.ts` | Emits the shared `FindManyParams<T>` type, the `encodeParams` helper, and the unexported `BaseRestClient` class |
| `src/render-root-client.ts` | Emits the `PrismaRestClient` aggregator with one property per model (e.g. `client.user`, `client.post`) |
| `src/generate-rest-client.ts` | Orchestrates all renderers and writes a single `index.ts` into the output directory |
| `src/generator.ts` | `RestApiClientGenerator` — implements the `Generator` interface (name `prisma-client-rest-api`, no required engines) |
| `src/index.ts` | Public package exports |
| `src/__tests__/fixtures.ts` | Shared DMMF model fixtures (a realistic `User` model and an id-less `Tag` model) |
| `src/__tests__/render-enums.test.ts` | 3 tests |
| `src/__tests__/render-model-interface.test.ts` | 8 tests covering interface, CreateInput optionality, UpdateInput, and WhereUniqueInput union |
| `src/__tests__/render-model-client.test.ts` | 9 tests covering HTTP verbs, path construction, and the no-id edge case |

### `tsconfig.build.bundle.json` updated
Added `"@prisma/client-generator-rest-api": ["./packages/client-generator-rest-api/src"]` for IDE go-to-definition.

### How the generated output looks
For a schema with `User` (id, email, name, role, createdAt) and `Post` models the generator writes a single `index.ts` containing:

```ts
// ----- Enums -----
export type Role = 'USER' | 'ADMIN'

// ----- Model interfaces and input types -----
export interface User { id: number; email: string; name: string | null; role: Role; createdAt: string }
export type UserCreateInput = { email: string; name?: string | null; role?: Role }
export type UserUpdateInput = { email?: string; name?: string | null; role?: Role }
export type UserWhereUniqueInput = | { id: number } | { email: string }

// Shared infra (FindManyParams<T>, encodeParams, BaseRestClient) ...

export class UserClient extends BaseRestClient {
  async findMany(params?: FindManyParams<User>): Promise<User[]> { … }
  async findUnique(where: UserWhereUniqueInput): Promise<User | null> { … }
  async create(data: UserCreateInput): Promise<User> { … }
  async update(where: UserWhereUniqueInput, data: UserUpdateInput): Promise<User> { … }
  async delete(where: UserWhereUniqueInput): Promise<User> { … }
}

export class PrismaRestClient {
  readonly user: UserClient
  readonly post: PostClient
  constructor(baseUrl: string, fetchFn = fetch) { … }
}
```

### Usage in a Prisma schema
```prisma
generator restApiClient {
  provider = "prisma-client-rest-api"
  output   = "./src/__generated__/rest-api-client"
}
```

Then register the generator in-process via:
```ts
import { RestApiClientGenerator } from '@prisma/client-generator-rest-api'
registry.add(new RestApiClientGenerator())
```

